<subSubSection pageId="7" pageNumber="54" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="7.[151,1436,260,457]" pageId="7" pageNumber="54">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,280,357,384]" pageId="7" pageNumber="54">Comments</emphasis>
. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Marusik, Ballarin &amp; Omelko" authorityYear="2012" box="[295,544,358,384]" class="Arachnida" family="Amaurobiidae" genus="Amaurobius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="7" pageNumber="54" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="koponeni">
<emphasis box="[295,544,358,384]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="54">Amaurobius koponeni</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was described based on the 
<typeStatus box="[869,967,358,384]" pageId="7" pageNumber="54">holotype</typeStatus>
male from 
<collectingRegion box="[1100,1258,358,385]" country="India" name="Uttar Pradesh" pageId="7" pageNumber="54">Uttar Pradesh</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[1270,1331,358,384]" name="India" pageId="7" pageNumber="54">India</collectingCountry>
. It seems that specimen was either mislabeled or brought by chance from 
<collectingCountry box="[876,927,394,420]" name="Italy" pageId="7" pageNumber="54">Italy</collectingCountry>
to 
<collectingCountry box="[964,1025,394,420]" name="India" pageId="7" pageNumber="54">India</collectingCountry>
. Judging from the shape of the male palp and size it is conspecific with 
<taxonomicName authorityName="L. Koch" authorityYear="1868" box="[544,670,431,457]" class="Arachnida" family="Amaurobiidae" genus="Amaurobius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="7" pageNumber="54" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="jugorum">
<emphasis box="[544,670,431,457]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="54">A. jugorum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and therefore the two names are synonymized here.
</paragraph>
