<subSubSection pageId="7" pageNumber="54" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="7.[151,1436,501,775]" pageId="7" pageNumber="54">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,280,568,595]" pageId="7" pageNumber="54">Comments</emphasis>
. This species was described based on a juvenile from 
<collectingCountry box="[901,1013,569,595]" name="Argentina" pageId="7" pageNumber="54">Argentina</collectingCountry>
and lacking any figures. Givven that there are no proven records of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="C. L. Koch" authorityYear="1837" box="[502,639,605,631]" class="Arachnida" family="Amaurobiidae" genus="Amaurobius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="7" pageNumber="54" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[502,639,605,631]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="54">Amaurobius</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
outside the Holarctic, this species is almost certainly misplaced in the genus and may belong to one of the few amaurobiid genera occurring in the Neotropical region. 
<bibRefCitation author="Lehtinen, P. T." pageId="7" pageNumber="54" pagination="199 - 468" refId="ref5910" refString="Lehtinen, P. T. (1967) Classification of the cribellate spiders and some allied families, with notes on the evolution of the suborder Araneomorpha. Annales Zoologici Fennici, 4, 199 - 468." type="journal article" year="1967">Lehtinen (1967: 212)</bibRefCitation>
supposed it belonged to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Lehtinen" authorityYear="1967" box="[477,625,677,703]" class="Arachnida" family="Titanoecidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="7" pageNumber="54" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Titanoecidae</taxonomicName>
, a family represented by two species belonging to one genus, 
<taxonomicName box="[1306,1396,677,703]" class="Arachnida" family="Titanoecidae" genus="Goeldia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="7" pageNumber="54" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1306,1396,677,703]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="54">Goeldia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="(Keyserling, 1891)" authorityName="Keyserling" authorityYear="1891" baseAuthorityName="Keyserling" baseAuthorityYear="1891" class="Arachnida" family="Titanoecidae" genus="Goeldia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="7" pageNumber="54" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="luteipes">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="54">G. luteipes</emphasis>
(Keyserling, 1891)
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="(Simon, 1892)" authorityName="Simon" authorityYear="1892" baseAuthorityName="Simon" baseAuthorityYear="1892" box="[505,822,713,739]" class="Arachnida" family="Titanoecidae" genus="Goeldia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="7" pageNumber="54" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="patellaris">
<emphasis box="[505,647,713,739]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="54">G. patellaris</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Simon, E." box="[664,813,713,739]" pageId="7" pageNumber="54" refId="ref6690" refString="Simon, E. (1892 a) Histoire naturelle des araignees. Vol. 1. Roret, Paris, 256 pp. https: // doi. org / 10.5962 / bhl. title. 51973" type="book" year="1892">Simon, 1892</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
. 
<taxonomicName box="[834,994,713,739]" class="Arachnida" family="Amaurobiidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="7" pageNumber="54" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Amaurobiidae</taxonomicName>
are not reported so far from 
<collectingCountry box="[1324,1436,713,739]" name="Argentina" pageId="7" pageNumber="54">Argentina</collectingCountry>
(WSC 2019). According to Lehtinen, the 
<typeStatus box="[616,664,749,775]" pageId="7" pageNumber="54">type</typeStatus>
is deposited in the Museo de La Plata.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
